This article is a transcript of a speech given by President Joe Biden at the L.A. Metro, D Line (Purple) Extension Transit Project in Los Angeles, California. In his speech, President Biden emphasizes the importance of unions and their role in building the middle class. He discusses his economic plan and efforts to combat inflation, including lowering gas prices and bringing down overall prices. He criticizes Republicans who argue that working people are making too much money and highlights his administration's focus on reducing costs for Americans. The President also discusses the significance of the Infrastructure Law and its impact on improving transportation, including the extension of the Purple Line and electrifying the bus fleet in Los Angeles. He mentions other infrastructure projects across California and expresses pride in the progress being made. President Biden concludes his speech by emphasizing his commitment to being a President for all Americans and his optimism about America's future.